<section id="about">
  <h1>Tibo Duran</h1>
  <div class="subtitle">
    Faculty | Chemical Engineering | Molecular Modeling & AI
  </div>
  <p>
    I am a faculty member in the Department of Chemical Engineering,
    with research interests at the intersection of molecular modeling,
    machine learning, and biomedical applications.
  </p>
  <p>
    My work focuses on developing computational and data-driven
    approaches to understand complex molecular systems and to enable
    advances in drug discovery, biomolecular engineering, and
    biopharmaceutical technologies.
  </p>
</section>

<section id="research">
  <h2>Research</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Molecular modeling and simulation of complex chemical systems</li>
    <li>Machine learning and AI for molecular and materials design</li>
    <li>Biopharmaceutical and biomedical engineering applications</li>
    <li>Multiscale modeling of transport and reaction phenomena</li>
  </ul>
</section>

